        <abstract>
            Priest Pot, a freshwater lake in the English Lake District. Its area is 1 ha and its maximum depth approximately 3.5 m.  The species list formed the basis of the publications:  Fenchel, T. &amp; Finlay, B. J. 2004. The ubiquity of small species: patterns of local and global biodiversity. BioScience 54:777-784  Finlay, B. J. &amp; Fenchel, T. 2004. Cosmopolitan metapopulations of free-living microbial eukaryotes. Protist 155:237-244.
        </abstract>
